Since, $$a\widehat i + \widehat j + \widehat k$$, $$\widehat i + b\widehat j + \widehat k$$ and $$\widehat i + \widehat j + c\widehat k$$ are coplanar.<br><br>$$\therefore$$ $$\left| {\matrix{
   a &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; b &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; c  \cr 

 } } \right| = 0$$<br><br>On applying C<sub>2</sub> $$\to$$ C<sub>2</sub> $$-$$ C<sub>1</sub>, C<sub>3</sub> $$\to$$ C<sub>3</sub> $$-$$ C<sub>1</sub>, we get<br><br>$$\left| {\matrix{
   a &amp; {1 - a} &amp; {1 - a}  \cr 
   1 &amp; {b - 1} &amp; 0  \cr 
   1 &amp; 0 &amp; {c - 1}  \cr 

 } } \right| = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow a(b - 1)(c - 1) - (1 - a)(c - 1) - (1 - a)(b - 1) = 0$$<br><br>on dividing by $$(1 - a)(1 - b)(1 - c)$$, we get<br><br>$${a \over {1 - a}} + {1 \over {1 - b}} + {1 \over {1 - c}} = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {{1 - 1 + a} \over {1 - a}} + {1 \over {1 - b}} + {1 \over {1 - c}} = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {1 \over {1 - a}} - 1 + {1 \over {1 - b}} + {1 \over {1 - c}} = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {1 \over {1 - a}} + {1 \over {1 - b}} + {1 \over {1 - c}} = 1$$

